The paper deals with improving the performance of predictive models when test and training data come from different distributions, which is a common problem in machine learning. The approach proposed in the paper, called test-time training, is applied to image classification benchmarks, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions self-supervised learning, which is a popular topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the theoretical investigations on a convex model suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
